irectional Characters\\n  }\\n\\n  /**\\n   * {@inheritDoc}\\n   */\\n  @Override\\n  public String prepareQuery(String string) {\\n    return Profile.super.prepareQuery(string);\\n  }\\n\\n  /**\\n   * {@inheritDoc}\\n   */\\n  @Override\\n  public String prepareStored(String string) {\\n    return Profile.super.prepareStored(string);\\n  }\\n\\n  /**\\n   * Non-ASCII space characters that can be mapped to SPACE (U+0020).\\n   */\\n  @Override\\n  public int[] additionalMappingTable(int codePoint) {\\n    // - non-ASCII space characters [StringPrep, C.1.2] that can be\\n    // mapped to SPACE (U+0020)\\n    return Tables.prohibitionNonAsciiSpace(codePoint)\\n        ? new int[] {0x0020}\\n        : new int[] {codePoint};\\n  }\\n\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777892539274}}\n619:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Inspecting SASLprep**\\n\\nI need to take a closer look at SASLprep. This seems related to string preparation for authentication, particularly with SASL (Simple Authentication and Security Layer). I'm curious about its purpose, like how it normalizes strings for compatibility across different platforms. I should make sure to gather all the necessary details and maybe check for best practices or common issues. I'll dive into the specifics and clarify any points that need attention!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_06ca08b8e191aa1b0169f87cb8561881a2b6662b83e19a2a20\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-Hy6__d8_l8KbPITXvQdY4NXEPNlWAU-42ukq8Z0_c_Oxsrjwz8tKV6ljGLgO7KtDWHKpDUdX_uH10Wi44GgIE8vOnKvM0_rLSRdOz1pHBolGBUw3t84G5UX2B7eH647su8Bmj6Hi662kI6xWH3yzMcnS-q9RRCLruPFS9rIBcSf1yc4VBR-mjSF0N-oZ1y6yAHn25FAll27kqhAJow6-YXCeTdB3EcrniJBI5W3otrVDHCUu2UZtDB62mc9LyA5WJfkDP-FaeqqbvgIzf2ozR1FACi2_Q8dhFJ9ynZJRwKhl-AYFKht3LwdgtWf3SIKFfSa0FmImCzJVKf9Rf1eVqyMkJcvJEJ0Pn-VpOQGc1puhissth9Ov8gfW0dvluYxTBVjFnl8XHznWNvmU40q3F